As more than 40 countries in Africa grapple with the spread of the novel coronavirus across the continent, a handful of others are relatively free of the fatal bugs that have killed more than 30,000 people out of the 500,000 plus infected across the world.
There are 13 African countries, across five regions, which have yet to confirm any positive, according to updates on WHO.
